In this article, President Trump meets with Shane Bouvet, a supporter who spent his last dime to attend the Inauguration. Shane's father, Donald, was suffering from cancer and Shane gave him the $10,000 that President Trump had given him. Donald used the money to receive treatment at a cancer clinic and is now cancer-free. President Trump praises Shane for his selflessness and calls it an incredible story. The President also briefly mentions the resignation of Mr. Porter and wishes him well. He confirms that a memo will be released soon.